                      <item xml:id="a01">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#1r"/>, upper right margin: Instruction for barren woman to recite Psalm 1
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a02">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#12v"/>, upper margin: “When the official or the king becomes angry with you, recite Psalm 19 over oil and anoint your face.” 
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a03">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#74v"/>: “When a husband and wife disagree, recite (this psalm, 118) over butter and anoint your body.” 
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a04">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#79v"/>, upper margin: in reference to Ps. 121 (E.T.) “When you experience no blessing, recite ‘I will look’ [this psalm] over water and sprinkle your house and also recite when you travel.” 
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a05">
                      <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                      <locus target="#107v"/>: Note of ownership, This book belongs to Mämǝre Wäldä Giyorgis
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a06">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#120r"/>:
                      A concluding prayer to the Psalter which mentions Archbishop Basǝlyos (1951–1959), Emperor Ḫaylä Śǝllase (5 May 1941–12 September 1974), and Empress Wälättä Giyorgis (Mänän, March 1889–15 Feb 1962).
                      Thus, the concluding prayer was written somewhere between 1951 and 1959.
                      The prayer is written in a well-trained hand and shows the essential elements of the genre,
                      <foreign xml:lang="gez">
                        ስብሐት፡ ለአብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ለዓለም፡ ወለዓለመ፡ ዓለም። ሰአሊ፡ ለነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ ማርያም። ምሕረተ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወልድኪ። የሐውጸነ፡ እምዓርያም። ሰአል፡ ለነ፡ ዳዊት። ቅድመ፡ መንበሩ፡ ለጸባዖት። ኦአምላከ፡ ዳዊት። አድኅነነ፡ እምዕለት፡ እኪት። ወባልሐነ፡ እምኲሉ፡ መንሱት። እለ፡ ወለዱነ፡ በሥጋ። ወእለ፡ ሐጸኑነ፡ በመንፈስ። ቅዱስ፡ ወእለ፡ አስተምሐሩነ፡ ቃለ፡ ሃይማኖት። ኅቡረ፡ ይምሐረነ፡ ይምሐሮሙ፡ በመንግሥተ። ሰማያት፡ ኦእግዚኦ፡ (እቀቦ)፡ ለጳጳስነ፡ ባስልዮስ ፡ ኦእግዚኦ፡ እቀቦ፡ ለንጉሥነ። ኃይለ፡ ሥላሌ፡ ኦእግዚኦ፡ ዕቀባ፡ ለንግሥትነ፡ ወለተ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ኦእግዚኦ፡ ዕቀባ፡ ለሀገሪትነ፡ ኢትዮጵያ። ኦእግዚኦ፡ ዕቀብ፡ ሕይወቶ፡ ወሥረይ፡ ኃጢአቶ፡ ለገብርከ፡ ወልደ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ኦእግዚኦ፡ ዕቀባ፡ ለዓመትከ። ወለተ ፡ ወልድ፡...(the concluding portion is covered by the painting on f. 120v)
                      </foreign>
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a07">
                      <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                      <locus target="#121v"/> in pen: Note of later ownership: “This bible belongs to Deacon Sǝyum.”
                      </desc>
