                      <item xml:id="e02">
                      <desc>
                      Psalm 118 contains the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e03">
                      <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#43v #55v #65r #83v"/>, etc.);
                      and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#16r #23v #50r #51v #63v"/>, etc.);
                      and in another case interlinearly where the symbol (┬) is used (<locus target="#62v"/>, line 19);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#60v #78r #102r #103r"/>);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#31r #39r #43r #90r"/>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e04">
                        <desc>
                          The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is
                          addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where
                          the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout)
                        </desc>
                      </item>

